HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 774
By Farmer
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Brittany Ramsey on
her selection as the 2025-2026 Sevier County
School System Grades 9-12 Teacher of the
Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Brittany Ramsey is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Ramsey has been selected as the 2025-2026 Sevier County School
System Grades 9-12 Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive
influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, in her ninth year as a teacher for grades 9-12, Brittany Ramsey served with
acumen and alacrity as an educator at Carter High School in Knox County and Sevier County
High School before coming on board with Gatlinburg-Pittman High School; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure, she has taught a variety of science and mathematics
courses, including honors and Advanced Placement (AP) physics and chemistry courses, and
she helped bring an expanded offering of courses to Gatlinburg-Pittman High School, including
AP Physics 1 and C: Mechanics; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Ramsey has also been involved in a number of programs and initiatives
throughout her career; she helped grow local Science National Honor Society chapters in the
region and brought a chapter to her current school, and she has contributed to chemistry and
physics curricula at various levels, serving on a district-level textbook adoption committee and
helping to ensure the implementation of new statewide standards; and
HJR0774
011256
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Brittany Ramsey is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who
works assiduously to motivate her students to reach their full potential, both as scholars and as
citizens; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Ramsey serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike,
and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Brittany Ramsey truly epitomizes the dedicated teacher who is wholly
committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate Brittany Ramsey on being chosen as
the 2025-2026 Sevier County School System Grades 9-12 Teacher of the Year, commend her
exceptional service to the children of Tennessee, salute her professional expertise and personal
excellence, and wish her all the best in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
